title: Renaissance

description.plain:
“Renaissance” is the opening track on Eminem’s 12th album The Death of Slim Shady (Coup De Grâce). The term “renaissance” originates from the Latin verb renasci, which means “be born again”. This concept symbolizes a thematic loop in the album, as it depicts Eminem/Slim Shady being lowered into his coffin in ”Somebody Save Me” after struggling to cope with addiction and overdosing in 2007.

In this short self-reflective track, Em channels his notorious reputation for controversial antics and voices his frustrations with critics and nitpickers of both the past and present rap eras.
